   Ladji  Doucoure  of France beat Olympic champion Liu Xiang of China in
   the final meters to claim the title of the men's 110 meters hurdles at
   the 10th world championships Helsinki on Friday.
   Doucoure,  who  led  the world this season with 12.97 seconds, won the
   race in 13.07 seconds.  Liu was second in 13.08.
   Four-time  world  champion Allen Johnson of the United States took the
   third in 13.10.
   
   Do you have confidence in his match in the future?
   Please give your own comments in English.
   
